You can connect to a MySQL database in PHP using the mysqli extension. Here's a basic example:$servername = ""localhost"";
$username = ""your_username"";
$password = ""your_password"";
$dbname = ""your_database"";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die(""Connection failed: "" . $conn->connect_error);
}

echo ""Connected successfully

To connect to a MySQL database in PHP, you can also use the PDO extension, which provides a more consistent and secure way to interact with databases:
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "your_username";
$password = "your_password";
$dbname = "your_database";

try {
    $conn = new PDO("mysql:host=$servername;dbname=$dbname", $username, $password);
    // Set the PDO error mode to exception
    $conn->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);
    echo "Connected successfully";
} catch (PDOException $e) {
    echo "Connection failed: " . $e->getMessage();
}
Replace your_username, your_password, and your_database with your actual database credentials and database name.

Another approach is to use the mysql extension (although it's deprecated as of PHP 5.5.0 and removed in PHP 7). Here's how you can use it:
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "your_username";
$password = "your_password";
$dbname = "your_database";

// Create connection
$conn = mysql_connect($servername, $username, $password);

// Check connection
if (!$conn) {
    die("Connection failed: " . mysql_error());
}

// Select database
mysql_select_db($dbname, $conn);

echo "Connected successfully";

// Remember to close the connection when done:
// mysql_close($conn);

Replace your_username, your_password, and your_database with your actual database credentials and database name. Also, please consider using mysqli or PDO instead of the deprecated mysql extension.

Remember that these answers assume that you have the appropriate MySQL server running on the specified host. Additionally, always ensure to sanitize and validate user inputs before using them in your queries to prevent SQL injection attacks.
